reviews.text: Delicious farm raised chicken, reasonably priced, good service.

Went again after a really long break. Got the recommended mala chicken dried noodle ... The chicken was kind of tough to chew,  but I guess it meant it wasn't fat ? The soup was pretty good, and the sauce was good. But the highlight being the chicken ... It was a bit of a disappointment

Really tasty even without MSG. We had the beef brisket noodles which were lean yet soft and flavorful and the fish combination balls, which were delightfully springy. We also had two servings of the sweet and fresh Choi Sum vegetables which were cooked to just the right texture. Will be back soon!
No MSG. Tasty beef brisket, fish ball, squid cake. Special dish: Sichuan spicy chicken dry noodle.
So good.
